external_knowledge:
- "sailing on the sea of their careers" - metaphorical expression referring to players who are still active professionally;
- "no end in sight" - indicates that the players' career_end_year and transfer end_year are null, meaning their careers and current team affiliations are ongoing;
- "more than five years" - calculated by adding the active period in the career and with the current team;
- The transfer fee acts as the cost of bringing a player to a team, akin to the 'salary' in this metaphorical context.

sql:
SELECT name, end_year - start_year AS years_of_experience
FROM coaches
WHERE end_year - start_year = (
    SELECT MAX(end_year - start_year) FROM coaches
);

SELECT start_year, end_year, transfer_fee
FROM player_teams
WHERE player_id = 1 AND team_id = 0 AND start_year >= 1990 AND end_year <= 2008;

SELECT coaches.name, teams.team_name
FROM coaches
INNER JOIN teams ON coaches.team_id = teams.team_id;
